botunban.description: 봇을 사용할 수 없는 사용자의 차단을 해제합니다.

createdm.description: 봇을 중개자로 사용하여 귀하와 사용자 사이에 DM을 만듭니다.

fixlinks.description: 아이돌/그룹에 잘못된 썸네일/아바타/배너를 수정하고 호스트에 게시합니다.

aliases.description: Lists the aliases of Idols/Groups that have one.
aliases.note: Underscores are spaces and commas are used to split Idol/Group names.

fullnames.description: 바트가 무슨 아이돌 사진을 있는 성명 리스트.
fullnames.note: ‘Bot Moderator’ 에겐, 사진 없는 아이돌을 보이면서 ID도 표시합니다.

groups.description: 봇이 사진이 있는 아이돌 그룹의 표시.
groups.note: 봇 중재자에게는 사진이 없는 그룹도 표시되고 ID도 표시됩니다.

members.description: 봇에 사진이 있는 아이돌의 이름을 나열합니다.
members.note: 봇 중재자에게는 사진이 없는 아이돌도 표시되고 ID도 표시됩니다.

sendidol.description: 봇은 12시간마다 문자 채널로 아이돌 사진을 보냅니다.
sendidol.note: 아이돌 ID 없이 명령어를 사용하면 채널에서 기존의 모든 아이돌이 제거됩니다.

sendimages.description: 모든 아이돌 사진이 특정 텍스트 채널에 나타나도록 합니다.

stopimages.description: 봇이 특정 텍스트 채널에 아이돌 사진을 게시하는 것을 중지합니다.

guessinggame.note: 게임 호스트는 stop 또는 end를 입력하여 게임을 종료하거나 skip을 입력하여 라운드 번호에 영향을 주지 않고 현재 라운드를 건너뛸 수 있습니다.

groupguessinggame.note: 게임 호스트는 stop 또는 end를 입력하여 게임을 종료하거나 skip을 입력하여 라운드 번호에 영향을 주지 않고 현재 라운드를 건너뛸 수 있습니다.

ggfilter.note: 필터링된 그룹만 추측 게임에 나타납니다. 그룹 ID 아니면 이름을 지정하지 않으면 필터가 토글됩니다. 그룹 ID와 이름은 쉼표로 구분해야 합니다. 단어가 두 개 이상인 그룹 이름에는 공백으로 밑줄을 사용해야 합니다.

ggleaderboard.description: Guessing 게임에 대한 서버/글로벌 리더보드를 표시합니다.

sendall.description: 로그 채널로 가는 모든 메시지를 토글합니다. 꺼져 있는 경우 편집 및 편집된 메시지만 보냅니다.

startlogging.description: Start sending log messages in the current server and channel.

stoplogging.description: Stop sending log messages in the current server.

addnoti.description: 서버에서 구문/단어가 언급될 때마다 DM을 받습니다.

botinfo.description: Displays general information about the Bot.

checkprefix.note: This command will always work with the bot's default prefix.

choose.note: Underscores are used for spaces between words. Spaces are used to separate choices.

invite.description: Bot을 서버에 추가하기 위한 초대 링크입니다.

listnoti.description: List all your notification phrases for the current server.

random.description: Choose a random integer from a to b.

removenoti.description: Remove a phrase/word from notifying you when it is said in the current server.

servercount.description: Shows the amount of servers connected to the Bot.

serverinfo.description: View information about the current server.

shard.description: Gets shard information about the current server.

stopgames.description: End all games that you are hosting or that are in the channel.

suggest.description: Suggest a feature for the Bot.

support.description: 봇의 지원 서버 디스코드 링크를 보냅니다.

vote.description: Direct link to vote for the Bot.

addalias.description: Add an alias to an idol/group.
addalias.note: Underscores for the alias are spaces. If a Bot Moderator uses this command, it will be a global (not local) alias.

clear.description: Prunes messages in the text channel.

deletealias.description: Delete an alias from an idol/group.
deletealias.note: Underscores for the alias are spaces. If a Bot Moderator uses this command, it will be a global (not local) alias.

disableinteraction.description: Disable an interaction on the server.
disableinteraction.note: To re-enable, use the same command again.

say.description: Make the Bot say a message.
say.note: If a text channel is not provided, it will send the message in the current channel.

sayembed.description: Make the Bot say an embed message.
sayembed.note: Follows the format from https://embedbuilder.nadekobot.me/. If a text channel is not provided, it will send the message in the current channel.

setprefix.note: Using the command with the default prefix (and no new prefix) will set it back to the default.

tempchannel.description: Make the current channel a temporary channel deleting messages after a delay.
tempchannel.note: The time delay must be greater than a minute. If the delay is -1, it will remove the channel as a temp channel. The delay must be put in seconds.

togglegames.description: Toggle the ability to play games in a text channel.

welcome.description: Set a welcome message in the current channel.
welcome.note: Use the command with no message to disable the welcome message. If the message contains %user, it will mention the user. If the message contains %guild_name, the server name will be added.

welcomerole.description: The role to give a user when they first join the server.

join.description: Makes the Bot join the current voice channel.

move.description: Make a song the next to play without skipping the current song.

play.description: Play a song based on a search query.

queue.description: Displays the currently queued songs in the player.

remove.description: Remove a song from the queue.

stop.description: Disconnects from the voice channel and resets the queue.

lyrics.note: The lyrics are retrieved from https://api.ksoft.si/

fm.description: Get information about a Last FM account.

recenttracks.description: Get the recent tracks of a Last FM Account.

recent.description: Get the most recent track of a Last FM Account.

topalbums.description: See the top albums of a Last FM Account.

topartists.description: See the top artists of a Last FM Account.

toptracks.description: See the top tracks of a Last FM Account.

setfm.description: 디스코드 계정에 LastFM 사용자 이름을 연결합니다.

deletetweet.description: Delete a tweet by it's ID.

tweet.description: Tweets a status update on Twitter.

twitterupdates.syntax: %twitterupdates <code/group/idol/list> <account username, group id, idol id> [role id]

code.description: Follow a Twitter channel based on the account username.

group.description: Follow a Twitter channel belonging to a Group ID If they have one.

idol.description: Follow a Twitter channel belonging to an Idol ID If they have one.

list.description: Lists the Twitter channels currently being followed in the text channel.

twitterupdates.note: This command contains sub-commands. This means any following arguments are respective to the first argument.

unscramble.description: Start an Idol Unscramble Game in the current channel.
unscramble.note: The host of the game can type stop or end to end the game or skip to skip the current round without affecting the round number.

usleaderboard.description: Shows Server/Global leaderboards for the Unscramble Game.

addrole.description: Add a role to be self-assignable.

listroles.description: List all of the self-assignable roles in the server.

removerole.description: Remove a self-assignable role based on the role name given.

sendrolemessage.description: Sends the default role message in the current channel.
sendrolemessage.note: The roles will work without this command, but should be used to have a list of roles.

setrolechannel.description: Set the channel for self-assignable roles to be used in.
setrolechannel.note: Since this command will erase all future messages, it is suggested to use %sendrolemessage before this one.

remindme.description: Create a reminder to do a task at a certain time.
remindme.note: The user input is fairly flexible for this command.

removereminder.description: Remove a reminder based on it's index.

settimezone.description: Set your local timezone with a timezone abbreviation and country code.
settimezone.note: The country code is the short-handed version of the location (ex: USA).

addtwitch.description: Adds a Twitch username to keep track of.

listtwitch.description: List the Twitch channels the server follows.

removetwitch.description: Remove a Twitch username that is being kept track of.

settwitchchannel.description: Set the Discord channel that the Twitch announcements will be posted on.

settwitchrole.description: Set the Discord Role that will be mentioned on Twitch announcements.

addcards.description: Fill the cards table with the default card names.

addpatreon.note: Use commas to separate user ids.

generateplayingcards.description: Generate Custom Playing Cards with Idol Avatars.

removepatreon.note: Use commas to separate user ids.

reload.description: Will hot reload all of IreneBot, IreneUtility, and any other self-made packages.

reloadmodule.description: Reload a module from it's name.

reloadutility.description: Reloads the utility package for the bot.

uploadfromhost.description: Toggles whether images are uploaded from the host or are used through an image url.

vliveupdates.syntax: %vliveupdates <code/group/idol/list> <channel code, group id, idol id> [role id]

code.description: Follow a VLIVE channel based on the channel code.

group.description: Follow a VLIVE channel belonging to a Group ID If they have one.

idol.description: Follow a VLIVE channel belonging to an Idol ID If they have one.

list.description: Lists the VLIVE channels currently being followed in the text channel.

vliveupdates.note: This command contains sub-commands. This means any following arguments are respective to the first argument.

addidol.description: Adds an Unregistered Idol using the syntax from https://irenebot.com/addidol.html.
addidol.note: Command should only be used if the card does not exist for the Idol.

addidoltogroup.description: Adds an Idol to a Group.

addgroup.description: Adds an Unregistered Group using the syntax from https://irenebot.com/addgroup.html.
addgroup.note: Command should only be used if the card does not exist for the Group.

edit.description: Edit an Idol or Group's information.

deleteidolfromgroup.description: Deletes an Idol from a Group.
